Step-by-step guide creating a docker container using Amazon Linux:

Prerequisites:
 - you will need to install docker
 - you will need to install git
 - I used Session Manager and changed from ssm-user to ec2-user

1. Update the package manager:
   sudo yum update -y

2. Install Docker:
   sudo yum install -y docker
   
3. Check docker version:
	docker --version

4. Check AWS CLI version:
	awscli --version
	- this is more of a habit rather than a requirement
	
5. Start the Docker service:
   sudo service docker start

6. Check the status of the Docker service:
   sudo service docker status

7. Enable the Docker service to start automatically on system boot:
   sudo systemctl enable docker

8. Add the current user (ec2-user) to the Docker group to allow running Docker commands without sudo:
   sudo usermod -a -G docker ec2-user
   - note I also changed the password of ec2-user and started using it instead of ssm-user.

9. Verify that you can run Docker commands without sudo:
   docker ps

10. Pull the "hello-world" Docker image:
	docker pull hello-world

11. Run the "hello-world" container:
	docker run hello-world

12. List the Docker images:
    docker images

13. List the Docker containers (both running and exited):
    docker ps -a

14. Remove the exited "hello-world" container:
    docker container rm 7cc5f2c049a2

15. Verify that the container has been removed:
    docker ps -a
